com.b2international.commons.db

Class PreparedQueryCollector<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.b2international.commons.db.PreparedQueryCollector<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the objects expected from the query result
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    PreparedQueryStringCollector

    public abstract class PreparedQueryCollector<T>
extends Object
    Executes a SQL query and places the results in a collection of objects of type T after conversion. Operations (including the constructor) may throw RuntimeSQLException to indicate failure related to the database.

      • collect

        public void collect(Collection<T> resultCollection,
                    Object... parameters)
        Executes the query with the specified parameters, and places the results into the given collection.

        When the object conversion and addition to the given collection is finished, afterProcessed() is called; if no row from the result set has been processed, or the result set is empty, onZeroResultsProcessed() is also invoked.

        Parameters:
        resultCollection - the collection to add elements to
        parameters - the variable number of query parameters

      • handleResultSet

        protected boolean handleResultSet(Collection<T> resultCollection,
                                  ResultSet resultSet)
                           throws SQLException
        Handles the conversion and addition of new objects to the collection based on the result set returned by the query. The default implementation calls forEachResult(Collection, ResultSet) for each resulting row, and stops processing if false is returned from that method.
        Parameters:
        resultCollection - the collection to add query result objects to
        resultSet - the result set returned by the query
        Returns:
        true if at least one result set row has been processed, false otherwise
        Throws:
        SQLException - if processing the result set fails for some reason

      • forEachResult

        protected abstract boolean forEachResult(Collection<T> resultCollection,
                                         ResultSet resultSet)
                                  throws SQLException
        Template method for extracting an object of type T from a single result set row and adding it to the collection; subclasses should override.
        Parameters:
        resultCollection - the collection to add the result object to
        resultSet - the result set returned by the query
        Returns:
        true if processing of result set rows should continue, false otherwise
        Throws:
        SQLException - if processing the result set row fails for some reason
